7 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of Kansas:
8 Section 1. K.S.A. 2024 Supp. 79-32,274 is hereby amended to read
9 as follows: 79-32,274. (a) For taxable years commencing after
10 December 31, 2020, and before January 1, 2026 2036, there shall be
11 allowed a credit against the tax imposed by the Kansas income tax act
12 and the privilege tax pursuant to K.S.A. 79-1106 et seq., and
13 amendments thereto, in an amount equal to 50% of the total amount
14 contributed during the taxable year by a taxpayer subject to income
15 tax pursuant to K.S.A. 79-32,110(a) or (c), and amendments thereto,
16 or subject to the privilege tax pursuant to K.S.A. 79-1107 and 79-1108,
17 and amendments thereto, to the Eisenhower foundation.
18 (b) The amount of such credit awarded to a taxpayer in a taxable
19 year pursuant to this section shall not exceed:
20 (1) $25,000 for any taxpayer subject to the income tax on resident
21 individuals imposed pursuant to K.S.A. 79-32,110(a), and amendments
22 thereto; or
23 (2) $50,000 for any taxpayer subject to the income tax on
24 corporations imposed pursuant to K.S.A. 79-32,110(c), and
25 amendments thereto, or the privilege tax on financial institutions
26 pursuant to K.S.A. 79-1107 and 79-1108, and amendments thereto.
27 (c) The aggregate amount of credits claimed pursuant to this
28 section shall not exceed $350,000 for any fiscal year.
29 (d) The credit allowed by this section shall not exceed the amount
30 of tax imposed under the Kansas income tax act or the privilege tax
31 reduced by the sum of any other credits allowable pursuant to law.
32 Such credit shall be deducted from the taxpayer's income or privilege
33 tax liability for the taxable year in which the contributions are made
34 by the taxpayer. The taxpayer shall not be allowed to carry over any
35 amount of such credit exceeding the taxpayer's income or privilege tax

